qSdiCFq4";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:279;s:6:"height";i:600;s:6:"source";s:108:"https://removeandreplace.com/2016/08/24/all-my-garage-door-openers-have-stopped-working-what-can-cause-this/";s:6:"domain";s:20:"removeandreplace.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:48:"electric garage door opener works intermittently";s:4:"slug";s:48:"electric-garage-door-opener-works-intermittently";s:5:"title";s:50:"How To Reset Garage Door Opener Unit Control Panel";s:3:"alt";s:29:"window covering manufacturers";s:3:"url";s:105:"https://www.wcmanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/How-To-Reset-Garage-Door-Opener-Unit-Control-Panel.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRG9Y7x2jniy__jShPx8MXUAs9LjJXz9Ie5qQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:600;s:6:"height";i:1000;s:6:"source";s:75:"https://www.wcmanet.org/how-to-reset-garage-door-opener-unit-control-panel/";s:6:"domain";s:15:"www.wcmanet.org";}}s:9:"sentences";a:60:{i:0;s:61:"Garage Door Opener Not Working or Intermittent Fix - YouTube.";i:1;s:51:"Garage Door Opener Not Working or Intermittent Fix.";i:2;s:57:"My electric garage door opener only works intermittently.";i:3;s:24:"It is a Genie H-4000-07.";i:4;s:53:"I have 3 wired buttons and then the remote in my car.";i:5;s:74:"All work fine for 2 or 3 days then none work for opening when I come home.";i:6;s:106:"Almost all mornings but not all it will work when I open the door from the wired button in my living room.";i:7;s:193:"When the garage door opener works intermittently the logic board may be experiencing radio frequency RF interference from nearby sources such as security lights ham radios and some electronics.";i:8;s:111:"If the remote works only when held within a few feet of the motor unit RF interference is probably the problem.";i:9;s:65:"As the garage door opens or closes it hits a white plastic lever.";i:10;s:89:"Under this lever is thin metal wire that gets pushed against a thin copper contact plate.";i:11;s:94:"This contact plate that gets triggered when the door opens must have gotten dirty or corroded.";i:12;s:71:"Garage Door Opener Working Intermittently - LED Bulb Culprit - YouTube.";i:13;s:96:"Fortunately the main cause of many automatic garage door problems is the electric opener itself.";i:14;s:91:"These can usually be quickly reset and should then begin working properly again in no time.";i:15;s:154:"If you think that your electric garage door opener needs to be reset the good news is that you can likely do this on your own in just a matter of minutes.";i:16;s:61:"In fact garage door opener remotes are not robust RF devices.";i:17;s:79:"Fresh batteries clean contacts on the batteries and on the buttons is critical.";i:18;s:134:"It isnt always easy to clean the buttons some are exposed others are enclosed but often times it is just oxidization and temp matters.";i:19;s:59:"Get shopping advice from experts friends and the community.";i:20;s:49:"I had a Sears Craftsmen Garage Door Opener Model.";i:21;s:62:"After 10 months remote would only operate door intermittently.";i:22;s:16:"All to no avail.";i:23;s:43:"Replaced receiver logic board assembly 209.";i:24;s:19:"Garage Door Opener.";i:25;s:188:"Works intermittently Radio interference from other devicessuch as photoelectric sensors for security lightscan prevent the garage door opener from responding to the signal from the remote.";i:26;s:34:"The problem is often intermittent.";i:27;s:83:"To test trigger the remote while standing close to the motor unitif the door opens.";i:28;s:169:"Many different electronic devices can cause radio frequency interference which will reduce the range of the garage door opener remote or cause it to work intermittently.";i:29;s:127:"Step by step process of elimination is the best way to determine what is causing the decreased range on the garage door opener.";i:30;s:51:"Why does my garage door opener work intermittently.";i:31;s:193:"When the garage door opener works intermittently the logic board may be experiencing radio frequency RF interference from nearby sources such as security lights ham radios and some electronics.";i:32;s:111:"If the remote works only when held within a few feet of the motor unit RF interference is probably the problem.";i:33;s:125:"Verifying that the door operates correctly and without excessive force with the opener disconnected is a required first step.";i:34;s:60:"If the door jams the opener cannot be expected to work well.";i:35;s:197:"Given a mechanically sound door system that operates properly by hand odd behavior in modern 25 years or less perhaps garage door openers is almost always a sign of time to replace the logic board.";i:36;s:102:"Sometimes people unplug their power source and then wonder why their garage door opener fails to work.";i:37;s:44:"Sounds ridiculous I know but it does happen.";i:38;s:72:"Make sure that your garage door opener is plugged into a working outlet.";i:39;s:25:"My garage door wont open.";i:40;s:34:"1 it has electric and new battery.";i:41;s:17:"2 its not locked.";i:42;s:29:"3 springs nor cable r broken.";i:43;s:148:"When you stand right under the opener it is like moving your radio to higher ground the opener has an easier time tuning in and activating the door.";i:44;s:243:"Sources of interference I have dealt with are old remotes in a drawer somewhere with something bumping a button televisions satellite systems a change in local phone or power lines airports military bases sprinkler timers radios and a host of.";i:45;s:89:"Also try unplugging the garage door opener and re-plugging the unit back into the outlet.";i:46;s:47:"This acts as a reset and may reset the sensors.";i:47;s:64:"If nothing works it may be that you have to replace the sensors.";i:48;s:107:"You can find new sensors on our Web site in the category section or by going directly to Infra-Red Sensors.";i:49;s:31:"The garage door closes down to.";i:50;s:84:"Your garage door opener is one of the unsung heroes in the world of home appliances.";i:51;s:55:"It works tirelessly day in and day out year after year.";i:52;s:135:"It ensures that you enjoy convenience that you dont have to get out in the rain or snow to open the garage door and it never complains.";i:53;s:193:"When the garage door opener works intermittently the logic board may be experiencing radio frequency RF interference from nearby sources such as security lights ham radios and some electronics.";i:54;s:111:"If the remote works only when held within a few feet of the motor unit RF interference is probably the problem.";i:55;s:23:"Below are the symptoms.";i:56;s:46:"Green LED on control console blinking rapidly.";i:57;s:29:"Sometimes works with remotes.";i:58;s:141:"Works with control console 95 of the time but when it openscloses lights on opener blink 2-3 times once door reaches open or closed position.";i:59;s:88:"Lights flash after a 1-2 second delay ie 1-2 seconds after reaching openclosed position.";}}